Turkey bought an estimated 100,000tonnes of white sugar from three trade houses today for Aprilto June shipment, according to trade sources.    They said a large U.K. trade house sold 50,000 tonnes, aU.S. house traded 25,000 tonnes, and a Swiss-based dealer house25,000 tonnes.    Price details were unclear but reports this morningsuggested that Turkey was offered sugar at prices ranging downto 212 dlrs a tonne, c and f basis. Reuter&#3;